latestPosts.caption:
@navneetrandhawa, the powerhouse behind Ambrosia Hospitality is a celebrated restaurateur, fashion tastemaker, and creative visionary based in Delhi. Her journey blends entrepreneurship, design, and culture—curating immersive experiences through food, art, and fashion.

From redefining iconic spaces like Amour Bistro and Town Hall to launching concept-driven ventures like Arts Room, Navneet’s influence spans far beyond the plate.

Prithviraj Jewels is honoured to collaborate with Navneet Randhawa for Timeless Faces of PRJ. Her multidimensional approach and refined aesthetic beautifully reflect the spirit of our heritage—where tradition meets modern artistry in every detail.

Clothing: @qua.clothing 

#TimelessFacesofPRJ #PrithvirajJewels

latestPosts.caption:
@bunka.in Some days move fast - from early errands to quiet moments in the sun, to dinners that linger a little longer.

I’ve always gravitated toward pieces that feel like me: soft, easy, but with a certain presence.

These Bunka pieces flowed with me through the day — from fine lace kurta set that breathe, to summer dresses that move, to elevated prints that carry just the right amount of drama.

Comfort, but always elevated. That’s the sweet spot.
•
#BunkaWoman #InBunka #DayToNightStyle #summersuits #summerdressing #summerfashion

An inspiring panel discussion with @vaishnavi.kumari and His Highness Brijesh Singh Ji of Kishangarh. We delved into the legacy @studiokishangarh , a renowned school of miniature painting, and discussed Princess Vaishnavi’s visionary efforts to bring this traditional craft into the mainstream. A truly enlightening conversation bridging heritage and innovation. 
Our stellar chefs @tworupeechef_  @breakin_desi and bartenders  @cocktailswithkk at @artsroomdelhi have curated a special menu inspired by the princely state of Rajasthan, think - Quail, laal Maas and a burst of flavours! 🤤

There’s just something about a man in a well-cut shirt.
Nothing says summer like crisp fabrics and clean lines — and Bombay Shirt Company’s new Khan Market store had just the palette we needed.
Shot this while building Randeep’s summer wardrobe — with ease, intention, and a whole lot of linen.
@bombayshirts #Custommade #Summer #Casuals #Linen #Mensfashion #Summervibes

We’re excited to share the latest art exhibit at Arts Room — a stunning collection from Studio Kishangarh, now on display in our gallery space. Watch along as Navneet Randhawa, Founder of Arts Room, and Princess Vaishnavi Kumari, Founder of Studio Kishangarh, dive into the stories and inspirations behind the collection.

Make sure to pair your visit with The Kishangarh Edit — a specially curated menu that features art on a plate and cocktails designed to complement the pieces on display, elevating your sensory journey.

Come for the art, stay for the flavors, and experience the perfect harmony of visual and culinary craft at Arts Room.

#ArtsRoom #StudioKishangarh #TheKishangarhEdit #ArtAndDining #SaketEats #CuratedExperiences #ArtExhibit #ArtOnAPlate

Pregnancy, Pandemic, and Everything In Between

Having babies during the pandemic meant isolation, uncertainty — and sometimes, deep grief.
Neha and Navneet open up about what it was like to go through some of their most vulnerable moments alone.
And Nanki reminds us: these stories matter. They stay in the body.

A quiet, powerful reflection on how the pandemic shaped motherhood — and maybe, our anxiety too.

🎧 Full episode: “Dear Mom(s), I get it now” | YouTube, Spotify, Apple Podcasts
#unparentpodcast #pandemicparenting #motherhoodunplugged #pregnancyjourney #covidbabies #maternalmentalhealth #momguilt #anxietyawareness #honestmotherhood
